              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value and are used to encapsulate reusable logic that can be applied to individual rows in a query. This function is designed to determine or calculate a specific value related to user access, specifically focusing on read-only access, and returns this value as a result."
